Description<a name="description"></a>
The Sales Data Centralization System is a project aimed at centralizing the sales data of our multinational company into a single, easily accessible database. The current sales data, scattered across various sources, hinders efficient analysis by team members. The goal is to create a unified and centralized repository, acting as the single source of truth for sales data. This system will enhance our organization's ability to be more data-driven, enabling quick and comprehensive access to up-to-date metrics for informed business decisions.

Installation Instructions<a name="installation-instructions"></a>
To install and set up the Sales Data Centralization System, follow these steps:

Clone the repository from [GitHub Repo Link].
Navigate to the project directory.
Run install.sh to install dependencies.
Configure the database connection settings in config.yaml.
Execute python setup.py to initialize the database.
Usage Instructions<a name="usage-instructions"></a>
After installation, follow these steps to use the Sales Data Centralization System:

Ensure the database is running and accessible.
Run the main application using python main.py.
Access the centralized sales data through the provided APIs or a web interface.
Use the documentation for API endpoints and queries.
